t deliberately gets off before. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1Vm1z2kgM%2Fisa5joHGUKMQ5qWGz6QxHmZ0msm5a5zEzJksWW81%2FWuZ3cdx5fmv5%2FWhgABPmEs6Vnp0SOtXxoRxiwX9lxF2Og3jo5gMBjAWDMuwSoINfuvpIdCwiT3vW4PCqVF9MSxgKI79afH0x40jVUZ9FoudCIJYmhMnmaWKwlhQkh98CBjWoUJZ8IBdT%2F70IWY6SkrWDlN8pRJszT4wCRPmTBTo1IsEmaXlmOIc5trXARMU2Yt6mnBbTKNuAlVLi2X86V7D6Rafz%2FdiK4yDViYAFulyw0wuC1tQs8xFwhEw8psjsC6dFgUmTZoJO64RANKV2AaD6lKliIlxQ29twnWBPxuKHMZVhh%2FQKjSTBmX6JsDxcoICZFe8To1Y5mMmFASIaXmiA48vnEfPD26VF04PmcYWgp8YiJHUHGFsGpTpwI7Q2NhlpeQu2NcoMH1wvowvAHDYrQlNO8wKpSK4I6cmA6TVo1xFfwZ3A3HwQXMSpijRM0sdrJyqQyMuN0g64CMbeqBrVNyfBJShXXBNWUNGMfuh8hG1wil58RUpqn7uoQZHRHzkNNzG86Cy293ATGhmagQCuTzxHWVeBHKaTXhj3X%2FhJpLpUlB8Nn7AOc30FSaqj5U8WHK5pLbPEI4%2BzYOzl1lRuXZF27DBOUFE%2BUt6r9MBAN4mUiADFUm8BpFhtGbxet4J%2B5Ar3PifAoUYoaUyRU10kHULl639vG6zqnSIOqYhTZn4ozJn39X%2FXKux3tOOtgBfQDNLhzug2tN5OtEzqONQlwuXm%2BRjOdPJEvjLYfjRUWeT%2Bkynm45LKvxqWabiA17t%2BM7a%2B%2BU2CyyTZPvec522qMkJrLgIprlc7Pp87H2%2BeRXPkyIGLdL8N8o17U%2B33lUdofgLTQW3BcXw9E%2FwJ5QuwHJSPi%2FPfTXpRZtyNDydDG0K5mFiowkQpT23WBROHu35yDLrXFq5tYJK1RuoAdw7%2Fr7AsQ79mHSGKmQpOlkBz9r3U0abSiit3L6kCKTzZ3CbJECuvDa3oS84k9Yj5Qod4Ota2I%2Fxg%2FSG7hlTuVo7nbB8Otlazfihop2Qw5vvsIRnC%2BwAmk1ZrToMNcm4dke2HXt7YYdU4eu3Q5HGCGb57gbaUOlDsnNrXdy%2Bmkb8XtCOycDKp%2FuJIRbrf4lLve0ZV3hFewW3A9SOd0chjAMNJM61YxWMAkpQrOH0O3Z2I0%2BHI0ug4s97L2bnX192b%2Frd%2BNujdwK%2BMGNm6YN5C60AYy4sR2NNHMGm9Ufo7Q9K5v1OLTh5dfzL3jurJ3x2qK9NXM31AAWQPfew2KKxzvvuPH1zffVKPah%2BkrgxPZsedHRkHPKwtAgrl2bdILzWD99Ihuv%2FwOrkQ%2FT" id="w1_2_3_4"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f6e0c0;strokeColor=#c9932a;fontColor=#5a3f10;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="875" y="239" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;▼ 47 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 5 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_3_4_5.drawio" id="w1_2_3_4_5"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f5d3b8;strokeColor=#cc7a33;fontColor=#5a300e;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="859" y="478" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Suffering-focused&lt;br&gt;ethics&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+6]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;(Brian Tomasik, David Pearce)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Asymmetry: averting intense suffering takes priority over creating happiness. Factory farming, malaria and the worst wild-animal conditions weigh up; speculative future-flourishing bets weigh down. Arises most naturally from taking animal suffering seriously, so it requires animals_somewhat. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 6 suffering_focused" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx9Vm1T4kgQ%2Fitd1G0dWIgBUW%2B54gNqfKllby2Xu60rseKQdMjcTmZSMxNjzvW%2Fb08CCgL7iZDufqb76ad78tyIMGa5sGcqwsagcXAAw%2BEQJppxCVZBqNn%2FJT0UEqZ5z%2Bv2oVBaRI8cCyi6QS84DPrBMTSNVRkct1zwVBLIyJg8zSxXEsKEsAbgQca0ChPOhIPqfuxBF2KmA1awMkjylEmzNPSASZ4yYQKjUiwSZpeWQ4hzm2tcBAQpsxZ1UHCbBBE3ocql5XK%2BdO%2BDVKvvg7XopdcxmDyOUVcOKswNRlURPgsTYG%2BVcAMMbkqb0HPMBQJx9GY2B2BdpiyKTBs0ErFcogGlKzCN%2B0QAS5Hy5Ybe2wRrbn43VJQMK4w%2FIVRppoyr4dWBYmWEhEivuKnQjGUyYkJJhJQ6Jzrw8NoY%2F%2FHBperC8SnD0FLgIxM5goorhLcediqwUzQWZnkJuTvGBRpcLWwAo2swLEZbQvMWo0KpCG7JiekwadUYl%2F5f%2Fu1o4p%2FDrIQ5StTMYicrl7LBiNs1svbI2Kb22DolxychVVjnXFPWgNQT%2BiGy0TVC6TkxlWkShi5hRkfEPOT03IZT%2F%2BLLrU9MaCYqhAL5PHENJ16EckJO%2BEPdP6HmUmkSF3z0PsDZNTSVpqr3VbyfsrnkNo8QTr9M%2FDNXmVF59onbMEF5zkR5g%2FpvE8EQnqcSIEOVCbxCkWH0avE63pE70OscOZ8ChZghZXJJjXQQtYvXrX28rnOq5Ik6ZqHNmThl8vs%2FVb%2Bc6%2BGOk%2Fa2QO9Bswv7u%2BBaU%2FkylfNorRCXi9dfJOP1ppKl8YbD4aIir0fpMp5uOCyr6VHNNhFr9m6n56z9E2KzyNZNPc9ztpM%2BJTGVBRfRLJ%2BbdZ%2Fj2uePXuXDhIhxs4TeK%2BW61uc7j8ruELyFxvy74nw0%2FhfYI2o3IBkJ%2F7f7warUojUZWp4uhvZNZqEiI4kQpX03WBTO3q1AyHJrnJq5dcIKlRvoIdy5%2Fj4D8Y4DmDbGKiRpOtnB91p300Ybiui1nAGkyGRzqzBbpABSDLy010Ev%2BSPWQyXK7XCrqvgVyjfSHLhdTyVp7vbB6PNFazvmmpIc6Cbk6PozHMDZAsuXVmNGyw5zbRKe7YBd1d%2BuXCfUpyu35BHGyOY5bsda02qN1T3qnhz2NwC%2FJrR4MqD66c5CuNHqP6JzR29WZV6hbsB9I6nT9WEIw0AzqTPNaA%2BTmiI0OxjdHJDt6KPx%2BMI%2F30HfuwHaxeCvVv525I3JW4W%2Bd3OnaRW5m20IY25sRyMNn8Fm9ccobU%2FLZj0XbXj%2B8fQDnjorp7y0aIHN3FU1hAXQnXe%2FGOfJ1stucnX99W0mB1B9SXBifLa88WjaOWVhaCJX7k86wXmsnj6VjZefPnAbXQ%3D%3D" id="w1_2_3_4_6"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f2ccc0;strokeColor=#c96a4a;fontColor=#5a2410;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="734" y="717" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Living in&lt;br&gt;a simulation&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+6+9]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;(Nick Bostrom)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + living_in_simulation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If most observers like us are simulated, the astronomical future that justified x-risk work probably gets switched off long before it happens. The same expected-value reasoning that bought astronomical stakes now attenuates them: future-facing value is multiplied by the probability the simulation keeps running, and the ranking slides back toward the present. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 6 suffering_focused → 9 living_in_simulation" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx9VmFT4zYQ%2FSs7mXaaMCE4JkBJJx8C%2BIBprsdwaW86hDGKvY7VkyWPJMekHP%2B9KzuBhCT9hNGunvbtvt3NSyPGhBXCXqoYG%2F3G0REMBgMYa8YlWAWRZv8u6KOUMCl8r9uDUmkRzzmWUHZDPzwOe%2BFpeA5NY1UO5y13fSIJZmhMkeWWKwlRSmh98CBnWkUpZ8KBdc996ELCdMhKtgjTImPSrAw%2BMMkzJkxoVIZlyuzKcgxJYQuNywthxqxFHZbcpmHMTaQKabmcrdx7INX6ebhxe%2BV1CqZIEtSVg4oKg%2FHKdA6Cz905l6HhWSGY41RRDFiUAnvnyQ0wuFvYlL4TLhAoh%2B9mcwTW8WBxbNqgkRLPJRpQugLTeEjpYRkSG27o3KZYZ%2B4XQ5RlVGH8BpHKcmUcwzcHuitjJEQ64qZCM5bJmAklETKqrOjA01vhgvmTC9Vdx%2BccI0sX50wUCCqpEN5r3KnALtBYmBYLKNwz7qLBdWJ9GN6CYQnaBTTvMS6ViuGenJiO0laNcR38EdwPx8EVTBcwQ4maWezki5WsMOZ2I1kHZGxT8WwdkssnIVVYV1xT1IBUMfpDyUZXCKVnlKlck2z0Aqb0RMIjTt9tuAg%2BfbkPKBOaiQqhRD5LnRwoL0I5oaf8qa6fUDOpNEkPzr2f4fIWmkoT60OVHGZsJrktYoSLL%2BPg0jEzqsh%2F5zZKUV4xsbhD%2FaeJYQAvEwmQo8oF3qDIMX6zeB3vxD3odU6cT4lCTJEiuaZCOojaxevWPl7XOVXiRZ2wyBZMXDD5%2Fa%2BqXs71eM9LBzugD6DZhcN9cK2JfJ3IWbxBxMXi9ZbBeP5EsizZcjheMvJ8CpfxbMthxcYnzjYVG%2FZux3fW3hlls8w3Tb7nOdtZj4KYyJKLeFrMzKbPae3zq1%2F5MCES3Kbgv6Vc1%2Fr84FHZHYK31FjwUF4NR38Dm6N2DZKT8H967K9LLd6QoeXZsmnfZRYpMpIIUdoPjUXX2YcBCXlhjVMzt05YkXINPYAHV98XoLxjHyaNkYpImk528L3W3aTRhjJ%2Bo9OHDJls7hRmixRAioHX9iboNZ9j3VRisRtuXRX%2Fh%2FKNNAduExAlzd08GH7%2B1NqNuaEkB7oNObz9DEdwucQKpNWY07DDQpuU53tg1%2FW3L9Yx1enGrQCEEbJZgbuxNrRaY3VPumfHvS3ArykNnhyIP200hDut%2FqF07qnNuswr1C24byR1Wh%2BGMAw00zrSnOYwqSlGsyej2w2yG304Gn0Krvak70MD1ay9XbXZP%2FN3Q2%2B13gb2o%2Bs8TcPI7bYBjLixHY3Ufgab1T9GaXuxaNad0YaXH88%2F4Lmz9sxri0bY1C2rASyBHrzHZUOPd6678c3t1%2Feu7EP1S4NTzqernUf9zikKQz25tkHpBeex%2FvpENl7%2FA3mSJvM%3D" id="w1_2_3_4_6_9"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#eeb3b3;strokeColor=#c0392b;fontColor=#5a1410;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1158" y="1195" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Person-affecting&lt;br&gt;view&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+6+9+11]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 6 suffering_focused → 9 living_in_simulation → 11 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx9VmFz4jYQ%2FSs7TDuFDCE2IUlDhw8k4ZJMuV4mR3vTCRlH2Gusnix5JBmH5vLfu7IhwQH6zWhXT7tv35N4aUQYs1zYSxVho984OoLBYAATzbgEqyDU7N8lfRQSpnnX83tQKC2iBccCCj%2FoBsdBLzgNzgPfh6axKgPfbzmIqSSooTF5mlmuJIQJIfbBg4xpFSacCQfon3fBh5jpgBVsGSR5yqRZB7rAJE%2BZMIFRKRYJs%2BvIMcS5zTWuNgQpsxZ1UHCbBBE3