t observers like us are simulated, the astronomical future that justified x-risk work probably gets switched off long before it happens. The same expected-value reasoning that bought astronomical stakes now attenuates them: future-facing value is multiplied by the probability the simulation keeps running, and the ranking slides back toward the present. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 9 living_in_simulation" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1lm1z4jYQx7%2FKDtNOIUOIcUhzocMLkpCHOa6XydHedELGEfYaqydLHknGobl8965sSCCYVyHs6qd9%2BO%2BKl0aEMcuFvVARNvqNoyMYDAYw0YxLsApCzf5b0odCwjT3vW4PCqVFtOBYQNEN%2FOA46AVn0DRWZXDWcoenkiBDY%2FI0s1xJCBNi9cGDjGkVJpwJh%2Bqe%2BdCFmOmAFWwZJHnKpFkbfGCSp0yYwKgUi4TZteUY4tzmGlcHgpRZizoouE2CiJtQ5dJyOV%2B790Cqze%2BDrdNrrzMQfOGsXAaGp7lgLvAyjxELE2DvyXADDO6WNqHPMRcIVKZ3szkC64JlUWTaoJFqyyUaULqEaTykGrAUKWRu6HubYFWe3wzlJcOS8QeEKs2UcWm8OdBZGSER6StuSpqxTEZMKImQUvNEB57eejNaPLlQ3XF8zjC0dHDBRI6g4pLw3sZOCTtHY2GWLyF317iDBjcT68PwFgyL0S6heY9RoVQE9%2BTEdJi0Ksb16M%2FR%2FXAyuoTZEuYoUTOLnWy5Vg5G3G4V64CMbeqQrUJy9SRSybrkmqIGjGP3h4qNrhFKz6lSmSZt6CXM6IqYh5w%2Bt%2BF8dPX1fkSV0EyUhAL5PHE9p7oI5bSc8Keqf0LNpdKkLzjzfoWLW2gqTVkfqvgwZXPJbR4hnH%2BdjC5cZkbl2WduwwTlJRPLO9R%2FmQgG8DKVABmqTOANigyjN4vX8U7chV7nxPkUKMQMKZJraqRDVC5et%2FLxus6pVCjqmIU2Z%2BKcyR9%2Fl%2F1yrsd7bjqoQR9AswuH%2B3CtqXydynm0lYiLxeutgvH8qWRpvONwvMrI8ylcxtMdh3U2PuVsE7Fl73Z8Z%2B2dUjWLbNvke56znfYoiKksuIhm%2Bdxs%2B%2Fxe%2BXzySx8mRIy7KfhvJdeVPj94lHZH8FYaGz0Ul8PxP8AWqN2AZCT8Xx77m1KLtmRoeboa2neZhYqMJEKU9sNg0XH2YQtCllvj1MytE1ao3EAP4MH19wWo7tiHaWOsQpKmkx38qHQ3bbShiN7S6UOKTDZrhdkiBXThtb2NvOYLrEZKLOthm5rYz%2FhOegO36ikdzd0uGH65atUTt1RUjxzefoEjuFixRtJqzGjRYa5NwrM92E3t1WMn1KEbt%2BERxsjmOdaTtlTqSG5uvZPTT7vEbwntnAwofXqxEO60%2BpdquactmwovsTu476RyejkMMQw0kyrUjFYwCSlCs6egu7NRTx%2BOx1ejyz3V%2BzA7Vdp1ndm%2F7evJO0O3iX50I6dpC7lHbQBjbmxHI82dwWb5j1Hani%2Bb1Ui04eXn80947mzc8tqi3TVzr9QAVqAH73E1yZPad25yc%2FvtfRz7UP6O4FTx2fqxo0HnFIWhYdx4OukG57F5%2B1Q2Xv8HIvwbxw%3D%3D" id="w1_2_3_4_9"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#eeb3b3;strokeColor=#c0392b;fontColor=#5a1410;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1438" y="1195" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Person-affecting&lt;br&gt;view&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+9+11]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 9 living_in_simulation → 11 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1Vu9z4jYQ%2FVd2mHYKGUJsQi4XOnwgCfkx5XqZHO1NJ2QcYa%2BxerLkkWQcmsv%2F3pUNCQ7wzWFXT7tv39PmpRFhzHJhL1SEjX7j6AgGgwFMNOMSrIJQs%2F%2BW9FFImOZdz%2B9BobSIFhwLKPygGxwHveAs8H1oGqsy8P2WA5hKAhoak6eZ5UpCmBBeHzzImFZhwplwcP5ZF3yImQ5YwZZBkqdMmnWgC0zylAkTGJVikTC7jhxDnNtc4%2BpAkDJrUQcFt0kQcROqXFou5%2Bv0Hki1%2BXtQO73OOgPBFy7KZWB4mgtWFr6u0ocMtVEyYHGMYQnjOCj7HLEwAfbeLDfA4G5pE%2FqOuUAgKt%2FD5gisa4ZFkWmDRuKfSzSgdAmm8ZA4YilSS9zQ7zbBir7fDPUtwxLjdwhVminj2nxLoLMyQkKkn7gp0YxlMmJCSYSUBiw68PQ2v9HiyZXqjuNzRk3RwQUTOYKKS4T3UXdKsHM0Fmb5EnJ3jTtocLOxPkwI68bRijBGNs%2BxOng9%2BnN0P5yMLmG2hDlK1Mx